{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_75","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n '\\\\[Lbyte;|\\\"byte\\\\[\\\\]\\\"|allPublicMethods|array' metadata tests/src docs schema -S\"","aggregated_output":"rg: schema: No such file or directory (os error 2)\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:94:Each artifact directory **must** include an `index.json` file (at `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`). This file is a JSON array of objects where each entry describes a specific metadata release.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:100:* `tested-versions`: An array of library versions verified to work with this specific metadata.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:101:* `allowed-packages`: An array of package prefixes. The TCK ensures that configuration entries (like reflection targets) belong strictly to these packages.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:105:* `requires`: An array of `groupId:artifactId` coordinates for libraries this metadata depends on.\ndocs/CONTRIBUTING.md:113:* `skipped-versions`: An array of objects (with `version` and `reason`) to explicitly exclude library versions known to be broken or incompatible.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:167:**4. Version-selection algorithm.** Given an application dependency `g:a:v`, native-build-tools loads the `index.json` array of `g/a/` and applies a primary lookup, picking the first entry that matches in this order:\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:176:    Start([\"Application dependency<br/>g:a:v\"]) --> LoadIndex[\"Load <code>g/a/index.json</code><br/>(array of entries)\"]\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:168:- Each local file contains the `versions` array for that metadata-version only\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/11.0.2/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:92:        List<String> arrayChanges = new ArrayList<>();\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/11.0.2/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:95:                arrayChanges.add(sizeChanged + \":\" + from + \"-\" + to));\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/11.0.2/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:106:        assertThat(arrayChanges).hasSize(4);\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/11.0.2/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:107:        assertThat(arrayChanges.get(0)).startsWith(\"false:1-\");\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/11.0.2/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:108:        assertThat(arrayChanges.get(1)).startsWith(\"true:3-\");\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:92:        List<String> arrayChanges = new ArrayList<>();\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:95:                arrayChanges.add(sizeChanged + \":\" + from + \"-\" + to));\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:106:        assertThat(arrayChanges).hasSize(4);\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:107:        assertThat(arrayChanges.get(0)).startsWith(\"false:1-\");\ntests/src/org.openjfx/javafx-base/13-ea/src/test/java/org_openjfx/javafx_base/Javafx_baseTest.java:108:        assertThat(arrayChanges.get(1)).startsWith(\"true:3-\");\nmetadata/com.google.api.grpc/grpc-google-common-protos/2.70.